May 16,1997<br>
It's 30 years later, 8 years of ptsd councling, and my eyes still fill with emotion each time I think of my tour.  We know what we did and what we were. We were proud american's that served when our country called. At 17, I didn't know if the government right or wrong. I only knew this is what a man was expected to do. I did know I could never live with the shame of not going.  I went, I was trained, I did what I was trained to do.  Regardless of what the S-2's, or A-3's say  I will always stand with pride for I spent my time in Hell!<br>

